{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Python Scripting"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["How to script Houdini using Python and the Houdini Object Model."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["The Houdini Object Model (HOM) is an application programming interface\n(API) that lets you get information from and control Houdini using the\n", {"text": ["Python scripting language"], "scheme": null, "type": "link", "exists": true, "value": "http://www.python.org/"}, ". HOM replaces the\nfunctionality of Houdini\u2019s previous scripting solutions,\nthe ", {"text": ["expression language"], "fullpath": "/expressions/index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/expressions/"}, " and ", {"text": ["HScript"], "fullpath": "/commands/index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/commands/"}, "."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["In Python, the ", {"text": ["hou package"], "fullpath": "/hom/hou/_index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/hom/hou/_index"}, " is the top of a hierarchy of modules, functions, \nand classes that define the HOM. The ", {"text": ["hou"], "type": "code"}, " module is automatically imported \nwhen you are writing expressions in the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, " \nand in the ", {"text": ["hython"], "type": "code"}, " command-line shell."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Overview"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["On Mac OS X, Houdini uses the system\u2019s Python."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "platform", "text": ["Mac"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["On Windows, Houdini uses the version of Python installed with Houdini."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "platform", "text": ["Windows"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["On Linux, Houdini does not look at ", {"text": ["$PATH"], "type": "code"}, " when trying to search and load the Python library. Instead it searches all the paths in ", {"text": ["$LD_LIBRARY_PATH"], "type": "code"}, ", then ", {"text": ["/lib"], "type": "code"}, ", and then ", {"text": ["/usr/lib"], "type": "code"}, ". If it can\u2019t find a suitable Python library in the system, it uses the one in ", {"text": ["$HFS"], "type": "code"}, ". If your Python library is not in a standard location, you should add its directory path to ", {"text": ["$LD_LIBRARY_PATH"], "type": "code"}, ". "]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "platform", "text": ["Linux"]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "platform_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Which Python?"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "subtopics_item", "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/hom/intro", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "intro"}]}, {"indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "subtopics_item", "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/hom/expressions", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "expressions"}]}, {"indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "subtopics_item", "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/hom/locations", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "locations"}]}, {"indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "subtopics_item", "text": [" ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/hom/tool_script", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "tool_script"}]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "subtopics_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Getting started"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "col"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "subtopics_item", "text": [" ", {"text": ["HOM cookbook"], "fullpath": "/hom/cb/index", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "cb/"}]}, {"indent": 4, "role": "it